  "text": "To analyze whether Notch signaling regulates the patterning of IC and PC proteins, we studied a conditional deletion of the Notch interacting domain exon 4 of Jag-1 [CITATION_1] . We deleted Jag1 with either Cdh16-Cre or Atp6b1-Cre-drivers and the deletions were confirmed at P60 by immunostaining (Figure 9-figure supplement 1 Figure 9 ; Figure 9 -figure supplement 2; n = 4 independent mice). Tubular structural failure was also found: tubules contained luminal debris ( Figure 9 figure supplement 2) and collecting duct diameter was enlarged 28% in Cdh16-Cre;Jag1 f/f (Aqp4 staining facilitated the measurements: 30.1 ± 3.5 mm vs 23.5 ± 2 mm, SEM, n = 4 independent mice, p=2Â10 À14 , Figure 9 -figure supplement 3). Krt8 was downregulated in these tubules, perhaps contributing to the structural failure. At later stages (P90) we observed hydronephrosis (3/4 mice), similar to another collecting duct-specific Notch-inactivation model [CITATION_2] . These data suggest that while expression of IC proteins are 'upstream' of Jag1, their relative level in specific cells of the collecting duct is controlled by Jag1 signaling.",
